
Webhooks
This group consists of the following endpoints:

Create or update a TikTok account Webhook configuration
Get TikTok account Webhook configurations
Delete a TikTok account Webhook configuration









Create or update a TikTok account Webhook configuration
Use this endpoint to create or update the configurations for Webhook events related to your TikTok account activities at the developer app level.

To learn more about how to create the configurations for these Webhook events, see Subscribe to TikTok account Webhook events via Webhooks API.

If you no longer wish to receive notifications, you can delete the Webhook configuration by using /business/webhook/delete/.

Request
Endpoint https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/business/webhook/update/

Method POST

Header

Field	Data Type	Description
Content-Type
Required
string
Request message type.
Allowed format: application/json.
Parameters

Field	Data Type	Description
app_id
Required
string
ID of your developer application.

You can find the App ID by navigating to My Apps > App Detail > Basic Information.
secret
Required
string
Secret of your developer application.

You can find the Secret by navigating to My Apps > App Detail > Basic Information.
event_type
Required
enum
The type of Webhook event that you want to subscribe to.

Enum values:
VIDEO: Post publishing events, which provide you with real-time updates on the status of content published via specific TikTok API endpoints.
To learn more about the schema and sample payload of the events within this event category, see Post publishing events.
COMMENT: comment update event, including the event comment.update.
To learn more about the schema and sample payload of the event within this event category, see Comment update event.
callback_url
Required
string
The callback URL.
item_list
string[]
Valid only when event_type is COMMENT.
Ignored when event_type is DEFAULT or VIDEO.

The IDs of the specific TikTok posts that you want to receive comment update event notifications for.

Max size: 100.

To obtain the IDs of TikTok posts under a TikTok account, use /business/video/list/.

When event_type is set to COMMENT and item_list is included in the request:
If item_list has never been configured for the developer app (app_id) previously, you will only receive notifications of comment.update events for the specified posts in item_list.
If item_list has been configured for the developer app (app_id) before, you will receive notifications for comment.update events of all previously configured posts in addition to the newly specified posts in item_list.
When event_type is set to COMMENT and item_list is not included in the request:
If item_list has never been configured for the developer app (app_id) previously, you will receive notifications of comment.update events for all posts under the TikTok account or TikTok accounts that authorized the developer app (app_id).
If item_list has been configured for the developer app (app_id) before, you will receive notifications of comment.update events for all previously configured posts. To review the specific posts configured for your developer app, check the item_list value in the response.
Example
Subscribe to post publishing events
curl --location --request POST 'https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/business/webhook/update/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "app_id": "{{app_id}}",
    "secret": "{{secret}}",
    "event_type": "VIDEO",
    "callback_url": "{{callback_url}}"
}'
Subscribe to the comment update event for all posts
curl --location --request POST 'https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/business/webhook/update/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "app_id": "{{app_id}}",
    "secret": "{{secret}}",
    "event_type": "COMMENT",
    "callback_url": "{{callback_url}}"
}'
Subscribe to the comment update event for specific posts
curl --location  --request POST 'https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/business/webhook/update/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "app_id": "{{app_id}}",
    "secret": "{{secret}}",
    "event_type": "COMMENT",
    "callback_url": "{{callback_url}}"
    "item_list": ["{{item_id}}", "{{item_id}}"]
}'
Update the callback URL for post publishing events
curl --location --request POST 'https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/business/webhook/update/' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "app_id": "{{app_id}}",
    "secret": "{{secret}}",
    "event_type": "VIDEO",
    "callback_url": "{{callback_url}}"
}'
